  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A new method is proposed for quenching the Eguchi-Kawai model. This new method avoids having to integrate over lattice momenta but retains much more manifest symmetry than the uniform division of the d -dimensional momentum hypercube into N sub-cubes. Furthermore our method has some big advantages for Monte Carlo calculations. We make some comments about the Wilson loop equations of the model and show how our method of quenching eliminates the unwanted “open loop” source terms. We show how our quenching prescription gives rise to a natural definition of a Fourier transformed loop space and derive some large N saddlepoint conditions which must be satisfied by the Fourier coefficients of the Wilson loops.</subfield>
